## 5. KTU 2024 Scheme Examination Question Bank & Topic Recap

### 5.1 PART A — Short Answer Questions (3 Marks Each)

---

**Q1. `[KTU University Exam – Dec 2023]`**
*Define an interface in Java. List any four characteristics of an interface.*

**Model Answer (3 Marks):**

An **interface** in Java is a reference type that defines a contract consisting of abstract method signatures and constants. It specifies *what* a class must do, not *how*.

**Four characteristics:**
1. Interfaces cannot be instantiated directly.
2. All methods are implicitly `public` and `abstract` (pre-Java 8).
3. All fields are implicitly `public static final` (constants).
4. A class can implement multiple interfaces, enabling multiple inheritance of type.

---

**Q2. `[KTU University Exam – May 2024]`**
*What is the difference between an interface and an abstract class? Mention any three differences.*

**Model Answer (3 Marks):**

| Feature | Interface | Abstract Class |
|---|---|---|
| Inheritance | Supports multiple inheritance | Supports only single inheritance |
| Fields | Only `public static final` constants | Can have instance and static fields of any type |
| Constructor | Cannot have constructors | Can have constructors |

