### Q2. [KTU University Exam – Jun 2024]
**What is a functional interface? Give one example.**

**Model Answer:**
A **functional interface** is an interface that contains **exactly one abstract method** (though it may also have any number of `default` or `static` methods). It is annotated with `@FunctionalInterface` (optional but recommended) and is the target type for **lambda expressions** and **method references**.
**Examples:** `Runnable` (with `run()`), `Comparator<T>` (with `compare(T,T)`), `java.util.function.Predicate<T>` (with `test(T)`).

