## KTU Examiner's Valuation Warning

> [!WARNING]
> **Common Pitfalls Where Students Lose Marks:**
> 1. **Forgetting implicit modifiers** — declaring `int MAX;` inside an interface without acknowledging it is `public static final` is a frequent deduction.
> 2. **Claiming interfaces support multiple inheritance of state** — Java interfaces support multiple inheritance of **type** only, **not state**. State is reserved for classes.
> 3. **Failing to override diamond conflicts** — students often leave the ambiguous `default` method unresolved and lose 2–3 marks.
> 4. **Writing constructors inside interfaces** — this is a compile-time error; examiners actively check this misconception.
> 5. **Confusing `extends` with `implements`** — interfaces `extend` interfaces; classes `implement` interfaces; classes `extend` classes.
> 6. **Omitting `@Override`** — not mandatory but examiners reward its presence for clarity.

