## Topic Recap & Important Things to Remember

- ✅ An **interface** is a pure **contract** declared with the `interface` keyword.
- ✅ All methods are implicitly `public abstract` (unless `default`, `static`, or `private`).
- ✅ All fields are implicitly `public static final`.
- ✅ A class **implements** one or more interfaces; an interface **extends** one or more interfaces.
- ✅ **Multiple inheritance** of *type* is supported only via interfaces in Java.
- ✅ **Default methods** (Java 8) provide backward-compatible evolution.
- ✅ The **diamond problem** requires explicit resolution via override or `I.super.m()`.
- ✅ **Functional interfaces** (exactly one abstract method) are targets for lambdas.
- ✅ **Marker interfaces** (zero members) tag classes with metadata/capability.
- ✅ Interfaces **cannot be instantiated** and **cannot have constructors**.
- ✅ Prefer an **abstract class** for shared *is-a* code/state; prefer an **interface** for *has-a* capabilities across unrelated hierarchies.
- ✅ Interfaces are the practical realization of the **Dependency Inversion Principle** (DIP) and the foundation of **loose coupling** in OOD.
- ✅ KTU 2024 frequently tests: *diamond problem, default methods, interface vs abstract class, multiple inheritance, marker interface, and functional interface*.

